58
00:06:55,525 --> 00:06:56,799
Am I glad you're here.

59
00:06:58,766 --> 00:07:01,642
Is that a '56 or a '57 Speedster?

60
00:07:02,085 --> 00:07:03,997
Fifty-six.

61
00:07:04,405 --> 00:07:07,364
Hey, come on, get out.
Will you get out of the car!

62
00:07:07,525 --> 00:07:08,799
Get away from there.

63
00:07:08,965 --> 00:07:11,525
- Took three weeks to build that fence.
- I'm sorry.

64
00:07:11,686 --> 00:07:14,199
Does this have a Super 90 engine
or a 1600?

65
00:07:14,366 --> 00:07:16,354
It wasn't really anybody's fault.

66
00:07:16,524 --> 00:07:18,799
My insurance will probably pay
for the fence...

67
00:07:18,964 --> 00:07:20,635
...and that should be fine. Okay?

68
00:07:20,804 --> 00:07:23,034
- Won't be the same.
- This ain't a kit car, is it?

69
00:07:23,204 --> 00:07:25,114
No, it ain't. It isn't.

70
00:07:25,683 --> 00:07:28,640
My name is Ben Stone.

71
00:07:28,843 --> 00:07:30,992
I'm a medical doctor.
I'm a surgeon.

72
00:07:31,162 --> 00:07:32,801
Awesome. Who thrashed the fence?

73
00:07:32,963 --> 00:07:35,395
I'm Ben Stone. Here's the address
of my clinic in L.A.

74
00:07:35,561 --> 00:07:38,157
- Did he say he's been stoned?
- He says he's from L.A.

75
00:07:38,323 --> 00:07:40,517
You can send a bill there
or we can use plastic.

76
00:07:40,682 --> 00:07:42,877
I'm not really from L.A.
I'm just on my way to...

77
00:07:43,042 --> 00:07:47,320
- You're lucky I was passing through.
- What's in the trunk? Pot?

78
00:07:48,641 --> 00:07:52,316
I'm a surgeon. Come on, will you
get away! Get away from the car!

79
00:07:52,481 --> 00:07:53,994
- Sorry.
- Not you, the dog.

80
00:07:54,161 --> 00:07:55,752
The finest fence I'll ever put up.

81
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:58,639
I know a Willie Stone in Stanton.
Is that family of yours?

82
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:01,632
- I understand what you're trying to do.
- This the new Mazda?

83
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,473
And I'm not putting up
with any small-town bullshit.

84
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,790
Where's the dang engine?

85
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:10,999
Get away from this car! You don't
even know where the engine is.

86
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:13,276
Got you.

87
00:08:15,279 --> 00:08:17,872
Look, I'm sorry
about what happened...

88
00:08:18,038 --> 00:08:21,748
...but it was an accident, okay?
It was nobody's fault.

89
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:25,114
Get me to a phone. I'll call
a Porsche mechanic in the next big city.

90
00:08:25,278 --> 00:08:29,237
I'll get my car fixed, be on my way,
and you can go back to doing...

91
00:08:29,398 --> 00:08:30,797
...whatever it is you do.

92
00:08:33,958 --> 00:08:36,629
All right, I admit it!
I flattened the damn fence!

93
00:08:36,796 --> 00:08:39,107
What are you gonna do, lock me up?

94
00:08:43,636 --> 00:08:47,868
Court finds the defendant guilty
of crimes under code 453-19...

95
00:08:48,037 --> 00:08:51,109
...reckless driving, and 466-2,
reckless endangerment.

96
00:08:51,276 --> 00:08:53,710
- This is insane.
- No, this is Grady.

97
00:08:53,876 --> 00:08:57,346
Your Honor, there were cows
in the middle of the road.

98
00:08:57,516 --> 00:09:01,110
Now, I told you my insurance company
would pay for a new fence.

99
00:09:01,276 --> 00:09:03,310
I built that fence myself.

100
00:09:03,475 --> 00:09:06,864
Neither you nor your insurance can
pay me for a fence I built myself.

101
00:09:07,034 --> 00:09:09,390
Next best thing would be
a fence that you built.

102
00:09:09,554 --> 00:09:13,467
- These hands are delicate instruments.
- I doubt you could build a good fence.

103
00:09:13,635 --> 00:09:15,749
Therefore, since you're
a licensed physician...

104
00:09:15,914 --> 00:09:18,508
...and we are a town in acute shortage
of medical care...

105
00:09:18,674 --> 00:09:21,632
- You wouldn't.
... your sentence will be 16 hours...

106
00:09:21,794 --> 00:09:23,227
...of community service...

107
00:09:23,394 --> 00:09:26,226
...served as resident doctor
at Grady Memorial Hospital.

108
00:09:26,393 --> 00:09:29,227
I have to be in Los Angeles
by Tuesday, so I don't...

109
00:09:29,394 --> 00:09:31,304
Thirty-two hours.

110
00:09:31,472 --> 00:09:34,384
- This is extortion!
- You want 64 hours?

111
00:09:35,672 --> 00:09:36,867
No.

112
00:09:37,752 --> 00:09:39,185
Court is adjourned.

113
00:09:39,353 --> 00:09:40,911
All rise.

114
00:09:41,591 --> 00:09:43,980
- I am so fucked.
- Watch your language, doc.

115
00:09:44,153 --> 00:09:49,146
You're in the buckle of the Bible belt
here. Try saying "fudge" or something.

116
00:09:49,431 --> 00:09:51,821
- "Fiddlesticks" too strong?
- Depends.

117
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:54,187
Don't you worry
about your automobile, doc.

118
00:09:54,351 --> 00:09:57,946
I always wanted an excuse
to buy me a set of metric tools.

119
00:09:58,112 --> 00:10:01,068
Sh... Sugar.

120
00:10:24,308 --> 00:10:25,788
Hey.

121
00:10:27,747 --> 00:10:29,227
I'm Dr. Benjamin Stone.

122
00:10:29,388 --> 00:10:33,016
Nurse Packer. I'm assuming
Judge Evans told you.

123
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,664
Fine. Here's what I need.

124
00:10:36,827 --> 00:10:40,820
Comfortable bed, hot shower,
warm meal, locker to put my stuff in...

125
00:10:40,988 --> 00:10:43,625
Could you show me some kind
of identification, please?

126
00:10:51,506 --> 00:10:54,736
I'm wearing glasses there.
I wear contacts now.

127
00:10:55,426 --> 00:10:57,576
My hair's a little shorter.

128
00:11:00,786 --> 00:11:04,334
That's a moustache.
It's a bad picture.

129
00:11:04,505 --> 00:11:07,940
If you could direct me to the physician
on call tonight, I'll speak to him.

130
00:11:10,865 --> 00:11:12,264
"When to call me:

131
00:11:12,425 --> 00:11:16,338
If you've been stabbed, shot, poisoned,
separated from an appendage...

132
00:11:16,504 --> 00:11:19,541
...knocked or beaten unconscious,
run over by a tractor, mower...

133
00:11:19,704 --> 00:11:22,901
...or generally about to bleed to death.
Otherwise, leave me alone."

134
00:11:23,063 --> 00:11:27,341
Signed,
Dr. Aurelius Edsel Hogue, M.D.

135
00:11:29,823 --> 00:11:32,018
I'm in The Twilight Zone.

136
00:11:34,262 --> 00:11:37,618
Zwieback and vitamin C
in the upper cabinet if you're hungry.

137
00:11:37,783 --> 00:11:41,297
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
This is the best you can do?

138
00:11:41,542 --> 00:11:43,134
No.

139
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:01,848
Oh, good, you're awake. Welcome
to Grady. I'm Mayor Nicholson.

140
00:12:02,020 --> 00:12:04,329
The second I heard
a big-city doctor was in town...

141
00:12:04,499 --> 00:12:07,297
...I left that rehearsal,
hightailed it over here...

142
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,655
...see if I can make you
more comfortable.

143
00:12:09,821 --> 00:12:11,936
- We can do better than this.
- Better than this?

144
00:12:12,099 --> 00:12:14,010
Say, these your duffles?

145
00:12:14,658 --> 00:12:18,571
I'm not claiming that Grady's no Paris,
France, but we got two gas stations...

146
00:12:18,739 --> 00:12:21,377
...got us a Winn-Dixie, got us cable TV.
Like tennis?

147
00:12:21,538 --> 00:12:25,134
We got a new tennis court at the high
school. You doctors play golf, though.

148
00:12:25,299 --> 00:12:27,813
- Learning how to surf, actually.
- Isn't this pretty?

149
00:12:27,978 --> 00:12:31,334
We had this fixed up for a doctor
we got through the want ads years ago.

150
00:12:31,497 --> 00:12:33,966
- No one's been in it for a while.
- Mayor Nicholson.

151
00:12:34,137 --> 00:12:37,447
I'm on my way to California.
Don't be thinking I'm staying here.

152
00:12:37,616 --> 00:12:39,893
No, no, of course not.

153
00:12:40,058 --> 00:12:42,366
Well, maybe not.
Give old Grady a chance...

154
00:12:42,536 --> 00:12:44,971
...she might sneak up on you
like a bee in a bottle.

155
00:12:49,456 --> 00:12:50,729
Surprise!

156
00:12:50,896 --> 00:12:53,250
- Welcoming committee.
- I hope you're hungry.

157
00:12:54,335 --> 00:12:55,736
Evening, ladies.

158
00:12:55,897 --> 00:12:59,570
Ben Stone, this here is Miss Violet
and Miss Lillian and Miss Maddie.

159
00:12:59,735 --> 00:13:02,932
Ladies, this here is Ben Stone, M.D.

160
00:13:03,095 --> 00:13:06,883
Fried chicken, boiled peanuts
and sweet potato pie.

161
00:13:07,055 --> 00:13:11,411
Catfish, biscuits, butter beans
and watermelon.

162
00:13:11,575 --> 00:13:14,566
Hungry-Man dinner. I'm a bad cook.

163
00:13:14,735 --> 00:13:18,727
Well, I guess I'll just say adieu
and come chauffeur you in the morning.

164
00:13:18,894 --> 00:13:20,804
No, wait, wait, wait. Come on.

165
00:13:20,974 --> 00:13:22,452
You can't leave me here...

166
00:13:22,613 --> 00:13:25,252
...in the middle of nowhere with them.
It's getting late.

167
00:13:25,412 --> 00:13:29,008
Don't worry. Only one of them horny.
I'm not telling you which one.

168
00:13:29,173 --> 00:13:31,163
Your face.

169
00:13:37,612 --> 00:13:39,921
You want a cocktail?

170
00:13:40,693 --> 00:13:44,923
So anyway, the high-profile,
high-profit work...

171
00:13:45,092 --> 00:13:48,002
...just makes it possible for me
to do the more important...

172
00:13:48,170 --> 00:13:51,719
...reconstructive surgery
for needier patients.

173
00:13:52,611 --> 00:13:54,886
And get a big house on the beach.

174
00:13:55,051 --> 00:13:59,442
It's hard to believe. A man as good-
looking as Dr. Stone should be married.

175
00:13:59,611 --> 00:14:01,647
Maybe he ain't found
his Adam's rib yet.

176
00:14:01,811 --> 00:14:05,644
Maybe he indulges in the love
that dare not speak its name.

177
00:14:05,809 --> 00:14:08,199
- Lillian.
- Will I go blind?

178
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:12,567
- It's moonshine, right?
- Well, ouzo, actually.

179
00:14:12,730 --> 00:14:15,960
- We took a cruise to Greece.
- Not me. I wasn't invited.

180
00:14:16,129 --> 00:14:18,848
It was one of those
golden-agers tours.

181
00:14:19,009 --> 00:14:20,920
Sunset Tours, honey.

182
00:14:21,088 --> 00:14:23,922
- They ate the brains out of a goat.
- Not me.

183
00:14:24,088 --> 00:14:26,318
- We ate dog.
- I didn't eat no dog.

184
00:14:26,487 --> 00:14:29,287
You don't know that you didn't.

185
00:14:29,608 --> 00:14:32,997
Dr. Stone, there's a legend
about friendship quilts.

186
00:14:33,168 --> 00:14:34,726
That's bunk.

187
00:14:34,888 --> 00:14:39,403
Folks say that the first person
to sleep under a friendship quilt...

188
00:14:39,567 --> 00:14:42,160
...will meet the one
they're gonna marry.

189
00:14:42,327 --> 00:14:45,319
Dream about the one they're
gonna marry, and it's bunk.

190
00:14:45,487 --> 00:14:48,559
What a fine hand he has.

191
00:14:49,406 --> 00:14:51,203
Dr. Stone?

192
00:14:52,206 --> 00:14:53,879
Dr. Stone?

193
00:16:04,599 --> 00:16:06,716
Oh, God.

194
00:16:28,437 --> 00:16:30,029
Hello.

195
00:16:31,797 --> 00:16:33,072
Hi.

196
00:16:33,878 --> 00:16:36,517
- Good morning.
- Is something wrong?

197
00:16:36,678 --> 00:16:38,871
No, no, no.

198
00:16:39,717 --> 00:16:41,355
I'm a doctor.

199
00:16:41,517 --> 00:16:43,904
Yeah, I know who you are.

200
00:16:45,797 --> 00:16:49,914
Hey, I'm sorry. Would you...?
Do you want this?

201
00:16:50,076 --> 00:16:53,910
If you're a doctor, I don't have
anything you haven't seen before.

202
00:17:04,036 --> 00:17:06,185
You can blink now.

203
00:17:10,595 --> 00:17:13,950
All the boys from the state legislature
come here, do their recreating.

204
00:17:14,114 --> 00:17:17,423
Boy, can they litter. Presidents
come here during the fishing season.

205
00:17:17,594 --> 00:17:19,506
On purpose?

206
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:22,990
One look at all this, Ben boy,
I'm sure you're saying to yourself:

207
00:17:23,153 --> 00:17:26,271
"I have come to Grady at the most
beautiful time of the year."

208
00:17:26,433 --> 00:17:29,469
But, boy, these dogwoods, azaleas,
when they blooming...

209
00:17:29,633 --> 00:17:33,307
...they can't hold a candle to the nuclear
explosion of color come fall.

210
00:17:33,473 --> 00:17:37,385
Nick, you're the mayor. You have
the authority to commute my sentence.

211
00:17:37,552 --> 00:17:39,066
Could you do that?

212
00:17:39,232 --> 00:17:42,144
I'll make it worth your while.
I get back to L.A., we could...

213
00:17:42,312 --> 00:17:44,950
Why on earth
would I wanna do that?

214
00:17:45,111 --> 00:17:48,467
How am I gonna convince you
to stay here if you're not here?

215
00:17:49,191 --> 00:17:52,740
We need a doctor, you need patients.

216
00:17:52,951 --> 00:17:57,024
Get off the interstate, Ben Stone.

217
00:17:57,512 --> 00:17:59,023
Right?

218
00:18:01,950 --> 00:18:05,306
Don't let the signs of prosperity and
urban sprawl in downtown scare you.

219
00:18:05,470 --> 00:18:07,539
We're still the same
sleepy little paradise...

220
00:18:07,709 --> 00:18:10,940
...that big-city shrinks recommend
for patients with nervous disorders.

221
00:18:11,108 --> 00:18:13,418
It's the calming effect
of Grady's natural ozone.

222
00:18:13,591 --> 00:18:16,182
Fact, there's a world-class
mental hospital up the road.

223
00:18:16,349 --> 00:18:17,623
That's a comforting thought.

224
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:21,464
Ben Stone, do you like coffee?
If you like coffee, we won't go in here.

225
00:18:22,909 --> 00:18:24,740
- Is that him?
- That's him.

226
00:18:24,908 --> 00:18:28,059
- He's young, huh?
- Come on, let's go.

227
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:33,024
Boys, this here is Ben Stone...

228
00:18:33,188 --> 00:18:36,181
...a Hollywood physician
who's gonna spend a few days with us.

229
00:18:36,348 --> 00:18:40,421
Ben, this is Mortimer, John, Aubrey.
Probably don't want to shake his hand.

230
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:43,464
Sorty in the corner.
Sorty got a cow that sings.

