until the situation stabilizes.

291
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:08,841
Yeah, medically speaking.

292
00:22:09,730 --> 00:22:12,084
You're interviewing other doctors?
Friday?

293
00:22:12,249 --> 00:22:16,720
Yeah, okay, Friday. I can do that. No,
thank you very much. And thank Doctor...

294
00:22:18,169 --> 00:22:21,843
That was better tap-dancing
than I've seen on Star Search.

295
00:22:23,888 --> 00:22:27,357
If you tell me you're here for
a physical, you're gonna make my day.

296
00:22:27,528 --> 00:22:30,168
It's unprofessional to flirt
with the patients.

297
00:22:30,328 --> 00:22:34,321
I'm just on my way to Beverly Hills.
Plastic surgery.

298
00:22:34,487 --> 00:22:36,240
Not that you need any.

299
00:22:36,408 --> 00:22:38,204
Nice try.

300
00:22:38,366 --> 00:22:41,916
So is this the GQ look
for young urban doctors?

301
00:22:42,926 --> 00:22:46,282
Well, I've spent the last two years
doing 18-hour days in the ER.

302
00:22:46,446 --> 00:22:49,722
I find these are pretty comfortable.

303
00:22:50,127 --> 00:22:51,957
You don't like them?

304
00:22:52,206 --> 00:22:53,764
No.

305
00:22:55,646 --> 00:22:59,082
Okay, fine. Well, I really enjoyed
our time together here...

306
00:22:59,246 --> 00:23:03,125
...but since you're obviously not a
patient, and I'm not getting anywhere...

307
00:23:03,285 --> 00:23:06,879
...tell me where I can find a guy named
Lou, drives an ambulance?

308
00:23:07,044 --> 00:23:08,717
I'm Lou.

309
00:23:17,803 --> 00:23:19,601
Where did all these people come from?

310
00:23:19,764 --> 00:23:22,880
Folks hear there's a doctor on duty,
they come running.

311
00:23:23,044 --> 00:23:25,433
Any old doctor.

312
00:23:28,123 --> 00:23:29,953
Send them in.

313
00:23:30,604 --> 00:23:33,640
Okay, Mr. Tidwell.

314
00:23:33,803 --> 00:23:36,236
What the hell have you got
on your foot?

315
00:23:36,402 --> 00:23:37,916
That's a poultice.

316
00:23:38,084 --> 00:23:41,835
- Nurse Packer!
- I got ahold to Doc Hogue on the CB...

317
00:23:42,002 --> 00:23:44,469
...and he said that that will hold me
till I came in.

318
00:23:44,642 --> 00:23:46,040
- You did this on purpose?
- Yes.

319
00:23:46,202 --> 00:23:49,274
It's chimney soot, biscuit flour
and lard. Doc Hogue said...

320
00:23:49,442 --> 00:23:54,561
Wipe that crap off Mr. Tidwell's foot,
please, and clean that wound out.

321
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:59,916
- You allergic to penicillin?
- Don't know. Ask Doc Hogue.

322
00:24:00,081 --> 00:24:03,117
Doubt Doc Hogue knows
it's even been discovered.

323
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:07,713
Okay. Nurse Packer,
I'm gonna wash this with Betadine...

324
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:11,918
...close it with a butterfly,
give it a sterile dressing.

325
00:24:12,079 --> 00:24:14,799
You sure you ought to be doing that
so darned fast?

326
00:24:14,958 --> 00:24:16,995
I hope so, Mr. Tidwell...

327
00:24:17,159 --> 00:24:19,115
...because je suis fini.

328
00:24:23,838 --> 00:24:26,990
Okay, Mrs. Owens, if you could
please get up on the table...

329
00:24:27,157 --> 00:24:28,672
...put your feet in the stirrups.

330
00:24:35,958 --> 00:24:37,912
We're just here about our mail.

331
00:24:38,397 --> 00:24:42,025
It's from my sister. We don't read.

332
00:24:44,676 --> 00:24:48,669
- This ever happen before, Mr. McClary?
- Hell, yes. It happens.

333
00:24:48,836 --> 00:24:51,146
This ain't nearly the biggest one
I ever took.

334
00:24:51,316 --> 00:24:55,275
I had a hook in my thigh once.
It must have been, I'd say, like...

335
00:24:55,435 --> 00:24:57,586
Oh, excuse me, I... Yeah, well...

336
00:24:57,755 --> 00:25:01,111
- Fishing's a dangerous business.
- Well, it can be.

337
00:25:01,275 --> 00:25:07,191
"And after the cow died, there just
wasn't any reason for him to go on.

338
00:25:07,754 --> 00:25:11,463
Meanwhile, Ellen's got herself
mixed up with a Pakistani gentleman...

339
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:14,911
...who nobody can understand
what he is saying.

340
00:25:15,474 --> 00:25:17,431
Not even Ellen."

341
00:25:17,714 --> 00:25:20,148
I don't see any toxic striations.

342
00:25:20,313 --> 00:25:21,748
Red streaks.

343
00:25:21,914 --> 00:25:24,428
You sure it was a black widow?

344
00:25:24,593 --> 00:25:28,744
Here. I kept it in some T.P.

345
00:25:30,313 --> 00:25:32,507
Oh, dear Lord, it's escaped.

346
00:25:34,672 --> 00:25:36,550
- There it is.
- Wait, there he goes.

347
00:25:36,713 --> 00:25:39,464
- Here he goes. Here he goes.
- Step on it.

348
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:42,385
"She thinks Ray's having an affair
with the pastor's wife...

349
00:25:42,551 --> 00:25:45,782
...but Ray swears
it's his scrub-up rash."

350
00:25:46,432 --> 00:25:49,423
Ray is a nut, I'm telling you.

351
00:25:49,672 --> 00:25:52,981
It's like a blurred spot
in my vision.

352
00:25:53,151 --> 00:25:57,985
Out there. No. There. No.
No, there.

353
00:26:09,069 --> 00:26:11,106
I'm cured.

354
00:26:11,550 --> 00:26:15,623
"The pastor's wife got busted
for growing marijuana...

355
00:26:15,790 --> 00:26:17,620
...out behind the rectory.

356
00:26:17,789 --> 00:26:22,943
So she'll be spending a spell up in Tupelo
at the minimum-security prison."

357
00:26:25,548 --> 00:26:27,584
That's it?

358
00:26:28,788 --> 00:26:31,428
What about Ellen and the Pakistani?

359
00:26:41,147 --> 00:26:43,216
Nurse Packer? Nurse Packer.

360
00:26:43,387 --> 00:26:47,140
Where's Doc Hogue? The boy can't
breathe right, and he's turning blue.

361
00:26:47,306 --> 00:26:48,580
I'm the doctor here.

362
00:26:49,307 --> 00:26:51,581
Nurse Packer,
you've got to call Doc Hogue.

363
00:26:52,145 --> 00:26:55,296
- Please.
- It's all right. I'm the doctor.

364
00:26:56,386 --> 00:26:58,660
- How long has he been like this?
- All afternoon.

365
00:26:58,824 --> 00:27:00,339
- What's his name?
- Zeb.

366
00:27:00,505 --> 00:27:03,144
Hey, Zeb, this is going to be
a little cold, all right?

367
00:27:03,306 --> 00:27:05,501
I just wanna hear your heart.

368
00:27:06,625 --> 00:27:08,502
Does your tummy hurt?

369
00:27:09,145 --> 00:27:12,692
All right, take him down to the
examination room. I'll be right there.

370
00:27:12,865 --> 00:27:15,503
You know where that is?
Right there, okay?

371
00:27:15,664 --> 00:27:18,224
Have Zeb get up on the table for me.

372
00:27:20,184 --> 00:27:22,903
- Call Hogue. Get him here.
- He doesn't like to be disturbed.

373
00:27:23,063 --> 00:27:25,975
I really don't care. Forget Hogue.
What's the referral hospital?

374
00:27:26,144 --> 00:27:28,055
- Athens General.
- Call Athens General.

375
00:27:28,223 --> 00:27:31,374
We have a cardiac emergency.
Tell Lou to fire up the ambulance.

376
00:27:31,544 --> 00:27:34,340
No, forget it. They have a helicopter.
Tell them to send it.

377
00:27:34,503 --> 00:27:38,212
- Get me Zeb's medical history.
- I better call Dr. Hogue.

378
00:27:38,382 --> 00:27:41,852
Damn it. Listen to me,
Hogue is not here. I'm here.

379
00:27:42,022 --> 00:27:43,820
You do it.

380
00:27:50,622 --> 00:27:52,215
Here's the situation.

381
00:27:52,381 --> 00:27:55,533
Your son is turning blue
because he has an abnormal mitral valve.

382
00:27:55,701 --> 00:27:58,977
It's causing a back flow of blood in
his heart. We may have to operate.

383
00:27:59,141 --> 00:28:00,699
We'll send him to Athens General.

384
00:28:00,860 --> 00:28:03,454
Dr. Hogue said
you should give the boy a Coke.

385
00:28:03,620 --> 00:28:08,136
He says he's probably got a bellyache
and that you should give him a Coke.

386
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:13,698
Listen, doctor, I've got a boy here
in cardiac crisis.

387
00:28:13,858 --> 00:28:17,738
You can't treat that with Coca-Cola or
Bisquick. We have to use real medicine.

388
00:28:17,899 --> 00:28:20,617
I'm sending him to Athens General.
You're his doctor...

389
00:28:20,778 --> 00:28:23,656
...so get your fat ass out of bed
and go with him!

390
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:29,365
- How long will the chopper be?
- Should be here any minute.

391
00:28:42,017 --> 00:28:44,578
- Where's Stone?
- Dr. Hogue.

392
00:28:45,297 --> 00:28:48,811
What the hell kind of snot-nosed
puppy doctor are you anyway?

393
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:52,093
Wake me up, scare these folks out
of their skivvies.

394
00:28:52,256 --> 00:28:54,406
Mitral valve regurge.

395
00:28:54,576 --> 00:28:58,568
I've had a lot of experience with it in ER.
I've even assisted in surgery to correct.

396
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:02,488
God only knows how long he's had this,
but you overlooked it. Check his color.

397
00:29:02,655 --> 00:29:04,725
Nurse Packer,
get that crap off the boy.

398
00:29:05,135 --> 00:29:08,047
Gene, you gave him the
bismuth subnitrate, didn't you?

399
00:29:08,216 --> 00:29:10,933
- At first we thought...
- You gave him too much as usual.

400
00:29:11,935 --> 00:29:14,129
Turned him three shades of blue.

401
00:29:14,294 --> 00:29:17,444
- Bismuth subnitrate?
- Homegrown antacid.

402
00:29:17,614 --> 00:29:19,843
You hear a heart murmur?

403
00:29:20,014 --> 00:29:21,605
No, it's hard to detect.

404
00:29:21,774 --> 00:29:24,652
You been sampling
your daddy's chaw?

405
00:29:31,534 --> 00:29:33,124
That will be 65 cents.

406
00:29:37,131 --> 00:29:39,725
Well, nice work, Hollywood.

407
00:29:39,892 --> 00:29:42,531
You were about to open
the chest of a 6-year-old boy...

408
00:29:42,691 --> 00:29:46,606
...to cure a case of diarrhea.
Now, listen up, smart-ass.

409
00:29:46,772 --> 00:29:49,206
Next time I tell you
how to treat a patient of mine...

410
00:29:49,372 --> 00:29:52,125
...you better damn well do it, doctor.

411
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:55,442
I doubt you'd know crap from Crisco.

412
00:30:05,451 --> 00:30:07,007
Hey.

413
00:30:09,130 --> 00:30:11,882
Yeah, right.

414
00:30:15,729 --> 00:30:18,641
Shit!

415
00:30:21,608 --> 00:30:24,282
Wait. Wait. Hold your horses, doc.

416
00:30:24,448 --> 00:30:28,044
Now, what if I walked in in the middle
of a hernia operation...

417
00:30:28,209 --> 00:30:31,166
...see some poor gentleman's guts
all over?

418
00:30:31,448 --> 00:30:33,722
- You killed my car.
- I resent that.

419
00:30:33,888 --> 00:30:36,799
That car was my life, Melvin.
That car was my baby.

420
00:30:36,966 --> 00:30:39,764
You want me to stop now?
I can put it in some boxes...

421
00:30:39,926 --> 00:30:42,999
...ship it out to Hollywood for you.
No skin off my nose.

422
00:30:43,168 --> 00:30:45,043
You and me called it
an oil pump casing.

423
00:30:45,206 --> 00:30:48,005
Lane had two years of the German
language in high school.

424
00:30:51,326 --> 00:30:53,396
Doc, let's step into my office.

425
00:30:56,165 --> 00:30:58,964
I don't need a car.
I'm moving to Los Angeles.

426
00:30:59,126 --> 00:31:01,959
- What do I need a car for?
- Lash yourself to the mast.

427
00:31:02,127 --> 00:31:05,435
Fella up in Oregon has an oil pump
he could air-express to us tomorrow.

428
00:31:05,606 --> 00:31:09,563
Two hundred thirty-nine bucks,
plus shipping. Only one problem.

429
00:31:09,765 --> 00:31:12,039
Oregon exploded.

430
00:31:12,204 --> 00:31:13,637
No.

431
00:31:14,165 --> 00:31:17,361
He don't take credit. Or checks.

432
00:31:17,525 --> 00:31:21,403
And tomorrow being Saturday,
you can't just wire some cash to him.

433
00:31:21,563 --> 00:31:24,362
Okay, Melvin, let me ask you this.

434
00:31:24,524 --> 00:31:27,878
How do you propose I pay for this?

435
00:31:28,043 --> 00:31:29,522
Well, I was hoping you'd pay me.

436
00:31:29,684 --> 00:31:33,722
Then I can trade him for a front rocker
assembly I got from a '68 Nova, but...

437
00:31:33,883 --> 00:31:37,557
- You don't take credit or checks.
- No, sir. I apologize.

438
00:31:37,723 --> 00:31:39,473
How long will this guy
in Oregon wait?

439
00:31:39,643 --> 00:31:42,474
I imagine I could stall him
till Sunday noon.

440
00:31:42,641 --> 00:31:47,032
Now, he got another taker in Arizona,
but I was first.

441
00:31:49,521 --> 00:31:51,193
Stall him.

442
00:31:55,401 --> 00:31:57,073
- Hi, doc.
- Hi, doc.

443
00:31:57,241 --> 00:32:00,630
- Morning, doc.
- Morning, Ben Stone.

444
00:32:00,802 --> 00:32:02,712
Howdy, y'all.

445
00:32:08,080 --> 00:32:11,628
- Dr. Stone. Dr. Stone, I presume.
- Yeah, that's right.

446
00:32:11,801 --> 00:32:13,198
- Hi.
- Hi.

447
00:32:13,359 --> 00:32:15,589
Say, you're much taller
than they said you were.

448
00:32:16,599 --> 00:32:19,159
I'm sitting on a stool.

449
00:32:20,319 --> 00:32:21,672
And you are?

450
00:32:21,839 --> 00:32:24,875
Dying to get out of this town.
How about you?

451
00:32:25,038 --> 00:32:27,155
- Here's your breakfast.
- I haven't ordered yet.

452
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:30,389
Compliments of the house.
Don't let old Hogue scare you off.

453
00:32:30,559 --> 00:32:33,833
We know you weren't aiming
to kill that boy last night.

454
00:32:34,518 --> 00:32:37,111
Wait a minute, you're not planning
on staying in Grady?

455
00:32:37,276 --> 00:32:39,916
- Only as long as I have to.
- Thank God.

456
00:32:40,077 --> 00:32:42,717
For a second, I thought they got
their hooks into you too.

457
00:32:42,878 --> 00:32:46,233
- Wait, you don't like Grady?
- No.

458
00:32:46,558 --> 00:32:48,070
So how come you don't leave?

459
00:32:48,917 --> 00:32:50,236
With you?

460
00:32:51,796 --> 00:32:53,674
Is that a proposition, doctor?

461
00:32:54,956 --> 00:32:57,344
I better eat this before it's cold.
Nice meeting you.

