00:47:51,962 --> 00:47:53,475
Then we moved to Manhattan...

706
00:47:53,801 --> 00:47:56,361
...you could hardly see any stars,
let alone count them.

707
00:47:56,521 --> 00:47:59,433
The stars I'd like to see
are more of the two-legged kind.

708
00:47:59,601 --> 00:48:01,832
Earthquake insurance
is something I'm keen...

709
00:48:02,001 --> 00:48:03,911
...to take a whack at out there in L.A.

710
00:48:04,080 --> 00:48:06,116
Talk about your no-brainer.

711
00:48:06,280 --> 00:48:10,319
Collect premiums for a gazillion years,
and if the big one ever does hit...

712
00:48:10,480 --> 00:48:13,357
...declare bankruptcy and retire.

713
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:17,831
- Decent and solid.
- Nobody's perfect.

714
00:48:17,999 --> 00:48:20,069
Hank, you gotta take Hogue home.

715
00:48:20,240 --> 00:48:22,547
He's about to launch
into "Song of Myself."

716
00:48:22,718 --> 00:48:24,517
My Lord.

717
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:27,597
Never a dull moment,
hey, Ben Stone?

718
00:48:27,759 --> 00:48:29,555
I'll call you later.

719
00:48:29,917 --> 00:48:31,556
Make sure you got home okay.

720
00:48:48,756 --> 00:48:51,226
- Good night.
- Night.

721
00:49:25,194 --> 00:49:28,185
- I forgot my pig.
- She's sleeping with Em.

722
00:49:28,353 --> 00:49:30,742
I'll drop her off in the morning.

723
00:49:31,152 --> 00:49:34,109
Greek death? Take the edge off.

724
00:49:34,272 --> 00:49:36,469
Take the edge off what?

725
00:49:37,912 --> 00:49:39,504
Me.

726
00:49:42,191 --> 00:49:47,107
- You ran all the way over here.
- Oh, yeah. I ran and...

727
00:49:47,272 --> 00:49:49,831
...walked. Got a stitch in my side.

728
00:49:49,992 --> 00:49:52,027
Why are you giving me
the full-court press...

729
00:49:52,192 --> 00:49:55,183
...if you're only leaving
in a couple of days anyway?

730
00:49:55,792 --> 00:49:57,382
You know, I don't know.

731
00:49:57,551 --> 00:50:02,466
It's like it's some kind
of mystical force.

732
00:50:02,632 --> 00:50:05,098
Force or hormones?

733
00:50:05,590 --> 00:50:07,740
Hey, come on.

734
00:50:07,910 --> 00:50:10,025
All I wanna do is talk.

735
00:50:12,270 --> 00:50:14,738
And get you sloppy drunk.

736
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:17,147
Honesty. That's a new approach.

737
00:50:17,309 --> 00:50:22,177
I know. You're forcing me
into uncharted territory here.

738
00:50:23,069 --> 00:50:25,821
Hell, I might even try chastity.

739
00:50:26,589 --> 00:50:29,147
Seems to work for Hank.

740
00:50:33,868 --> 00:50:35,938
Speak of the devil.

741
00:50:38,307 --> 00:50:41,822
Listen, maybe a rain check?

742
00:50:43,505 --> 00:50:46,783
I never should have accepted
those flowers.

743
00:50:51,627 --> 00:50:53,140
What about tomorrow night?

744
00:50:53,306 --> 00:50:55,900
Desperation. I like this.

745
00:50:57,385 --> 00:51:03,700
Still, I wouldn't want the mayor to have
to lose 10 bucks over me, you know?

746
00:51:23,583 --> 00:51:24,902
Morning.

747
00:51:27,583 --> 00:51:29,335
Funny. Funny.

748
00:51:33,663 --> 00:51:37,779
Morning, doc.
That's a nice pig you got there!

749
00:51:38,102 --> 00:51:39,981
Yeah, that's what they tell me.

750
00:51:40,143 --> 00:51:45,262
Hey, Mr. McClary, be careful you don't
get another hook in your finger!

751
00:51:45,422 --> 00:51:50,097
Don't worry, doc.
We're not using hooks today.

752
00:52:01,500 --> 00:52:03,889
It's all right. It's all right.

753
00:52:10,180 --> 00:52:14,172
- He's a nice pig, doc.
- It's a she, actually.

754
00:52:18,580 --> 00:52:20,694
Relax, will you?

755
00:52:22,019 --> 00:52:24,897
House calls are probably
my favorite part of the job.

756
00:52:25,060 --> 00:52:29,849
Just driving out into the country, seeing
what might pop up around the next bend.

757
00:52:30,578 --> 00:52:32,490
Rainbows.

758
00:52:32,738 --> 00:52:34,535
Frost on the kudzu.

759
00:52:35,257 --> 00:52:39,614
John Muir said it, "Most people
are on the world, not in it."

760
00:52:43,218 --> 00:52:44,492
What?

761
00:52:45,656 --> 00:52:47,408
Nothing.

762
00:52:50,097 --> 00:52:51,735
What?

763
00:53:04,655 --> 00:53:07,489
Listen, you better let me handle
this one alone.

764
00:53:07,656 --> 00:53:10,532
- Obstetrical exam.
- Okay.

765
00:53:11,455 --> 00:53:14,605
"So Jimmy Joe went over to
the Pakistani's house with a shotgun."

766
00:53:14,774 --> 00:53:18,084
Excuse me.
Jimmy Joe is Ellen's brother?

767
00:53:18,254 --> 00:53:20,324
No, no. Boyfriend.

768
00:53:20,854 --> 00:53:23,005
I was stumped on that one too.

769
00:53:23,174 --> 00:53:26,211
"He stayed outside shooting holes
in the fella's foreign car...

770
00:53:26,374 --> 00:53:29,205
...until Ellen came out and agreed
to come back home with him.

771
00:53:29,374 --> 00:53:32,570
It's the most romantic thing
Jimmy Joe has ever done for her."

772
00:53:38,333 --> 00:53:39,765
Tough one.

773
00:53:39,932 --> 00:53:43,367
How's Ellen making out
with the Pakistani man?

774
00:53:46,252 --> 00:53:47,765
Get him, get him. Come on, Bubba.

775
00:53:50,171 --> 00:53:53,847
I said... I said, no shots.

776
00:54:03,730 --> 00:54:05,528
This won't hurt.

777
00:54:05,690 --> 00:54:08,363
Well, I don't see an infection.

778
00:54:08,610 --> 00:54:10,327
But...

779
00:54:12,810 --> 00:54:14,879
Okay, hold still.

780
00:54:18,970 --> 00:54:21,528
- What is that, a V8?
- He did it.

781
00:54:24,010 --> 00:54:27,523
You know, house calls used to be
essential to every doctor's practice.

782
00:54:27,688 --> 00:54:30,600
The only way to know your patients
was to see where they live.

783
00:54:30,768 --> 00:54:32,758
How they lived.

784
00:54:33,447 --> 00:54:35,119
Maybe when I get to Halberstrom's...

785
00:54:35,288 --> 00:54:38,199
...I'll get them to institute some kind
of visitation program.

786
00:54:38,368 --> 00:54:39,643
Damn it.

787
00:54:44,087 --> 00:54:45,725
Lou?

788
00:54:48,927 --> 00:54:50,484
Hey, Lou!

789
00:54:53,925 --> 00:54:56,520
Do you see another one?
They mark their way with these.

790
00:54:56,685 --> 00:55:00,565
They're too stupid or too drunk to
remember where they were most times.

791
00:55:00,726 --> 00:55:03,160
- Who?
- Hunters.

792
00:55:03,805 --> 00:55:06,923
Maybe this is the end of...
Yeah. See, there it is.

793
00:55:07,086 --> 00:55:09,440
That's where they sit
and wait for the slaughter.

794
00:55:09,605 --> 00:55:13,836
It's not like they do it for food either.
God, it gets me so hot.

795
00:55:18,684 --> 00:55:20,914
You wanna help me here?

796
00:55:21,404 --> 00:55:22,756
What are you doing?

797
00:55:23,682 --> 00:55:25,083
I'm urinating.

798
00:55:26,483 --> 00:55:29,317
You just drop trou
whenever you feel like it.

799
00:55:29,484 --> 00:55:33,317
Well, it scares the deer away
so the hunters won't get them.

800
00:55:35,202 --> 00:55:37,842
Why don't you just, you know,
say "boo" or something?

801
00:55:38,003 --> 00:55:41,676
I try to spread it around.
A little here, a little there.

802
00:55:43,241 --> 00:55:45,516
Feel free to join in.

803
00:56:07,321 --> 00:56:10,995
Anyway, it's not like I planned
to be pregnant at 19...

804
00:56:11,159 --> 00:56:13,151
...but it could have been worse
than Wayne.

805
00:56:13,320 --> 00:56:15,390
Wendall Barnes.

806
00:56:15,559 --> 00:56:16,878
You'd be interested in him.

807
00:56:17,039 --> 00:56:20,111
He comes from a whole family
that doesn't have sweat glands.

808
00:56:20,279 --> 00:56:23,271
Really? I'm fascinated
by the gland-less.

809
00:56:23,439 --> 00:56:24,713
I guess it's genetic.

810
00:56:24,878 --> 00:56:28,233
During the summer, they all sleep under
the house on account of the heat.

811
00:56:28,397 --> 00:56:31,594
That's a touching story. Really.
Thanks for sharing that with me.

812
00:56:31,757 --> 00:56:35,352
You don't see a lot of things in Grady,
but what you do see, you see a lot of.

813
00:56:35,517 --> 00:56:37,474
Yeah, I'm from a small town myself.

814
00:56:37,918 --> 00:56:39,509
What?

815
00:56:40,918 --> 00:56:45,432
Marionville, Indiana.
Population: 2106.

816
00:56:45,597 --> 00:56:48,588
Home of the world's largest
steam engine.

817
00:56:49,076 --> 00:56:50,668
But you told everybody that you...

818
00:56:50,836 --> 00:56:54,545
No, no, no. Everybody assumed
I was a big-city guy.

819
00:56:54,715 --> 00:56:56,946
Nobody asked.

820
00:56:57,116 --> 00:56:59,629
Anyway, I got out,
and I'm staying out.

821
00:57:01,956 --> 00:57:04,470
Have you still got
your whole family there?

822
00:57:04,635 --> 00:57:06,944
Well, they talked about leaving...

823
00:57:07,115 --> 00:57:09,753
...but my dad never quite...

824
00:57:10,794 --> 00:57:12,991
They lived there, they died there.

825
00:57:13,154 --> 00:57:15,304
For better or for worse.

826
00:57:15,795 --> 00:57:19,992
So when I left home, I swore
to myself I was never going back.

827
00:57:20,914 --> 00:57:23,474
It's not the place, it's the person.

828
00:57:24,393 --> 00:57:27,510
Be careful what you wish for,
Ben Stone, you might get it.

829
00:57:27,714 --> 00:57:29,192
What's that supposed to mean?

830
00:57:29,353 --> 00:57:31,913
You never been back,
not even to see your friends?

831
00:57:32,073 --> 00:57:35,191
Well, who's got time for friends?

832
00:57:39,552 --> 00:57:42,783
No, you gotta get Dr. Stone
back here ASAP.

833
00:57:42,951 --> 00:57:45,022
We got a possible
coronary emergency.

834
00:57:45,191 --> 00:57:49,025
- Can't Doc Hogue handle this?
- It is Hogue. Over.

835
00:57:52,751 --> 00:57:55,107
- Hey, lie down.
- Oh, crap, I'm doomed.

836
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:57,382
Lie down now.
You're having a heart attack.

837
00:57:57,551 --> 00:57:59,507
My angina's acting up is all.

838
00:57:59,670 --> 00:58:02,707
- Got any nitro pills down there?
- No, get a bolus of lidocaine.

839
00:58:02,870 --> 00:58:05,146
I'm the senior sawbones around here.

840
00:58:05,311 --> 00:58:08,541
PVCs are too close to your T-waves.
In 30 seconds, you're in trouble.

841
00:58:08,710 --> 00:58:10,109
Get him away from me.

842
00:58:10,270 --> 00:58:13,819
If I'm wrong, lidocaine won't hurt.
If you're wrong, it's a ventricular fib.

843
00:58:13,990 --> 00:58:15,548
I'm never wrong.

844
00:58:17,029 --> 00:58:19,384
Get the defibrillator over here.

845
00:58:19,628 --> 00:58:21,029
Never wrong.

846
00:58:21,229 --> 00:58:23,184
Four hundred watts.

847
00:58:23,469 --> 00:58:24,743
Clear. Clear!

848
00:58:27,269 --> 00:58:28,826
Heartbeat.

849
00:58:28,989 --> 00:58:32,219
- Sixty.
- Wow, you mean he actually has one.

850
00:58:32,388 --> 00:58:34,856
Keep him on oxygen
and set the lidocaine drip.

851
00:58:35,908 --> 00:58:37,818
Guess I'm staying here tonight.

852
00:58:50,666 --> 00:58:52,180
Oh, doctor.

853
00:58:52,348 --> 00:58:54,576
I've got your bed ready.

854
00:58:56,707 --> 00:58:58,185
Right.

855
00:59:02,186 --> 00:59:03,459
Sleep well, doctor.

856
00:59:11,546 --> 00:59:13,820
At which point, all the bees,
including Melvin...

857
00:59:13,984 --> 00:59:16,373
...lunged off the edge
of the stage like lemmings.

858
00:59:16,544 --> 00:59:19,298
- A standing ovation.
- Variations on a theme.

859
00:59:19,465 --> 00:59:20,816
Sorry I missed it.

860
00:59:20,983 --> 00:59:24,293
That's the first squash pageant
that I missed in 15 years.

861
00:59:24,463 --> 00:59:25,817
What's going on here?

862
00:59:25,983 --> 00:59:29,896
It's called moral support
for the recovering patient.

863
00:59:30,063 --> 00:59:31,496
Cherry cobbler, Ben?

864
00:59:31,663 --> 00:59:35,576
Everybody out. Let's go.
Come on, visiting hours are over.

865
00:59:35,742 --> 00:59:40,258
Don't mind Doc Hollywood. He doesn't
know what it means to be beloved.

866
00:59:42,062 --> 00:59:45,577
If you've come to clean the room,
my bedpan's ripe.

867
00:59:50,101 --> 00:59:53,299
Oh, no.
Not Maddie's sweet potato pie.

868
00:59:53,461 --> 00:59:56,021
You can razz me all you want, doc.

869
00:59:56,462 --> 00:59:59,099
I saved your life last night.

870
00:59:59,341 --> 01:00:02,173
You know it, and I know it.

871
01:00:03,100 --> 01:00:04,818
Gotcha.

872
01:01:32,934 --> 01:01:35,970
Dr. Halberstrom, please.
It's Ben Stone calling.

873
01:01:36,813 --> 01:01:38,963
It's regarding...

874
01:01:39,493 --> 01:01:43,964
I'm not gonna be able to make
my interview on Friday.

875
01:01:44,533 --> 01:01:49,525
I realize the doctor has a tight schedule.
I'm not gonna be able to leave without...

876
01:01:51,492 --> 01:01:52,766
Right.

877
01:01:52,932 --> 01:01:56,845
Is there any way that he can reschedule
the appointment for another time?

878
01:01:57,570 --> 01:02:00,211
All right. Thanks a lot.

879
01:02:28,249 --> 01:02:31,557
Here you go. Get hot and take a shot.
Get hot and take a shot.

880
01:02:31,729 --> 01:02:33,320
What's the object of this one, pal?

881
01:02:33,489 --> 01:02:35,761
Ten shots a dollar.
Five bull's-eyes win a possum.

882
01:02:35,927 --> 01:02:39,396
- Suppose I was to hit five out of five.
- I'll give you two possums.

883
01:02:47,766 --> 01:02:52,318
Sir, run Henry a tab.
He feels deadly today.

884
01:02:54,606 --> 01:02:57,040
Evening, Dr. Stone.

885
01:03:09,684 --> 01:03:11,004
Hey, doc.

886
01:03:13,763 --> 01:03:16,802
The new one's in.
Your chariot's good as new.

887
01:03:16,965 --> 01:03:19,273
Or good as new used, since it's old.

888
01:03:19,444 --> 01:03:22,243
- You fixed my car?
- Even all the ashtrays.

889
01:03:22,403 --> 01:03:24,519
Oh, man, I can't believe this.

890
01:03:24,683 --> 01:03:25,957
Melvin, thanks, man.

891
01:03:28,123 --> 01:03:29,840
There's always some extra parts...

892
01:03:30,003 --> 01:03:32,313
...when I put them back together.
I don't know why.

893
01:03:32,484 --> 01:03:35,679
But you go ahead on. Keep them.

894
01:03:40,083 --> 01:03:42,232
- Dance with me or I'm dog food.
- What?

895
01:03:42,402 --> 01:03:45,634
- Wendall Barnes.
- Of the gland-less Barnes?

896
01:03:45,802 --> 01:03:48,031
- Jesus.
- Yeah. Come on.

897
01:03:48,202 --> 01:03:50,396
Absolutely.

898
01:04:05,121 --> 01:04:06,873
You see, the trick...

899
01:04:07,480 --> 01:04:11,473
...is just to visualize the target
on the backs of your eyeballs...

900
01:04:11,639 --> 01:04:16,393
...and then pretend you're just
shooting yourself in the eye.

901
01:04:23,599 --> 01:04:25,794
I can't keep up.

902
01:04:43,718 --> 01:04:45,355
How's Hogue?

903
01:04:45,517 --> 01:04:47,109
Meaner than ever.

904
01:04:53,836 --> 01:04:55,589
Dance?

905
01:05:01,595 --> 01:05:03,506
Where's Hank?

906
01:05:03,755 --> 01:05:05,586
I forget.

907
01:07:03,146 --> 01:07:05,137
The music stopped.

908
01:07:05,665 --> 01:07:07,496
What music?

909
01:07:11,304 --> 01:07:13,023
Dr. Stone.

910
01:07:13,465 --> 01:07:16,537
- I have a present for you.
- Thanks, judge.

911
01:07:16,704 --> 01:07:20,458
I want to thank you for saving
my old friend Hogue's miserable life.

912
01:07:20,624 --> 01:07:22,819
I wouldn't be able
to call myself a Christian...

913
01:07:22,983 --> 01:07:25,658
...if I didn't pardon you
on the remainder of your sentence.

914
01:07:25,824 --> 01:07:27,780
You're free to go
whenever you want.

915
01:07:27,943 --> 01:07:30,059
What I wouldn't give to be young
on the road...

916
01:07:30,223 --> 01:07:32,943
...footloose and fancy-free.

917
01:07:33,102 --> 01:07:36,175
Did I tell you? I've already got plans
for a new fence.

918
01:07:36,343 --> 01:07:38,616
All of a sudden,
I got a bug in my ear...

919
01:07:38,782 --> 01:07:41,899
...for one of those solid-oak numbers
with curly tops.

920
01:07:44,263 --> 01:07:45,899
Victory.

921
01:07:46,062 --> 01:07:48,212
Did you kill that critter
all by yourself?

922
01:07:48,381 --> 01:07:49,815
Very funny.

923
01:07:49,981 --> 01:07:54,532
Don't you have some urgent business
thousands of miles away from here?

924
01:07:54,700 --> 01:07:58,534
Vialula, your daughter was dumping
grasshoppers in the punch bowl again.

925
01:07:58,701 --> 01:07:59,771
Only two.

926
01:07:59,941 --> 01:08:05,492
- Shake a leg with the judicial branch?
- Why, I'd love to. Thank you.

927
01:08:06,060 --> 01:08:07,460
Would you hold this possum?

928
01:08:07,620 --> 01:08:11,010
I think it's time I reacquainted
your mama with some real dancing.

929
01:08:11,180 --> 01:08:13,740
No offense, Hollywood.

930
01:08:19,260 --> 01:08:21,727
When you gonna bring
your pig back around?

931
01:08:30,858 --> 01:08:33,656
Hey there, Ben Stone.
Hey, how are you?

932
01:08:33,818 --> 01:08:35,933
Been looking for you.
What a great day.

933
01:08:36,097 --> 01:08:38,566
Boy, this is it.

934
01:08:38,738 --> 01:08:42,014
The pinnacle of existence,
the grandeur of Grady.

935
01:08:42,177 --> 01:08:44,327
Sap of life.
Couldn't be happier if I was twins.

936
01:08:44,497 --> 01:08:48,285
- You put on a hell of a festival, mayor.
- Ain't you nice to say so.

937
01:08:48,457 --> 01:08:52,244
Ben, let's talk turkey.
Or squash, as it were.

938
01:08:52,417 --> 01:08:54,691
- About what?
- Home.

939
01:08:54,856 --> 01:08:56,130
Heart.

940
01:08:56,297 --> 01:08:57,776
Happiness.

941
01:08:57,937 --> 01:08:59,607
You belong here, Ben Stone.

942
01:08:59,777 --> 01:09:03,564
Breaks my heart to think of you
out there in the land of lunatics.

943
01:09:03,735 --> 01:09:06,966
I'm danged if I'll let you go
without holding up a mirror to your face.

944
01:09:07,135 --> 01:09:11,014
Like that smile of contentment there.
So you see that? See there?

945
01:09:11,175 --> 01:09:15,213
That's a face that's liked and loved.
A face with friends and a future.

946
01:09:15,375 --> 01:09:17,763
Can't find some other way
to force me to stay?

947
01:09:17,934 --> 01:09:19,253
Ben.

948
01:09:19,413 --> 01:09:21,210
I am everything but devious.

949
01:09:21,373 --> 01:09:24,765
Mayor, could you come check
these ribs and tell me if they're done?

950
01:09:24,933 --> 01:09:26,605
I sure can.

951
01:09:26,774 --> 01:09:28,888
Rigors of the job, huh?

952
01:09:29,293 --> 01:09:33,490
Well, you got your fire way too high,
I'll tell you that.

953
01:09:33,972 --> 01:09:35,292
Well, don't do that.

954
01:09:37,293 --> 01:09:40,249
Come on, come on.

955
01:09:42,692 --> 01:09:44,922
- Hi, doc.
- Gentlemen.

956
01:10:20,209 --> 01:10:22,403
Careful with those things.

957
01:10:38,607 --> 01:10:42,362
I know I shouldn't be doing this because
you're leaving, but I don't care.

958
01:10:42,527 --> 01:10:44,359
I can't help it.

959
01:10:44,528 --> 01:10:46,119
So get in.

960
01:10:46,407 --> 01:10:50,285
- Do you mean what I think you mean?
- Just get in if you're gonna get in.

961
01:10:56,527 --> 01:10:59,246
Lou, I gotta be honest with you.

962
01:10:59,406 --> 01:11:02,158
Rowing a boat is not
what I had in mind.

963
01:11:06,365 --> 01:11:08,003
Not bad, huh?

964
01:11:11,285 --> 01:11:12,557
Incredible.

965
01:11:14,324 --> 01:11:16,599
- What was that?
- Freshwater mullet.

966
01:11:16,763 --> 01:11:20,837
They see the sparks from the skyrockets,
think it's food and jump for it.

967
01:11:21,004 --> 01:11:22,960
That's scary.

968
01:11:23,204 --> 01:11:25,159
Maybe I could...

969
01:11:25,644 --> 01:11:27,760
...sit next to you,
and you could protect me.

970
01:11:27,924 --> 01:11:29,959
No. You'll throw us off balance.

971
01:11:30,123 --> 01:11:32,272
I want you off balance.

972
01:11:32,443 --> 01:11:34,354
- He's in the boat!
- Hold still.

973
01:11:34,524 --> 01:11:36,434
- Get him.
- Watch it, you'll tip us over.

974
01:11:36,603 --> 01:11:38,673
- Get him, Lou.
- Okay, I got it.

975
01:11:43,281 --> 01:11:45,591
You did that on purpose.

976
01:11:46,522 --> 01:11:48,956
All right, I admit it.

977
01:11:49,403 --> 01:11:53,076
I worked my way through college
by training bass.

978
01:12:15,720 --> 01:12:17,038
Lou?

979
01:12:17,558 --> 01:12:19,390
It's okay.

980
01:12:20,200 --> 01:12:22,554
Listen, if you don't wanna...

981
01:12:23,079 --> 01:12:26,957
Ben, I don't think I've ever wanted
anything more in my entire life, ever.

982
01:12:27,638 --> 01:12:30,914
I'm just not used to being
a one-night stand.

983
01:12:33,518 --> 01:12:36,475
You don't have to be.
I mean, I could...

984
01:12:36,678 --> 01:12:40,192
No. I wouldn't know what to do
with myself in Los Angeles.

985
01:12:40,357 --> 01:12:42,792
There are too many choices.

986
01:12:44,277 --> 01:12:46,836
Let's not think about it, okay?

987
01:12:52,236 --> 01:12:54,306
I can't do this.

988
01:13:05,995 --> 01:13:10,433
Mind walking from here? I don't wanna
give the gossips any more fat to chew.

989
01:13:12,874 --> 01:13:14,546
Right.

990
01:13:15,355 --> 01:13:18,266
Don't worry, Benjamin,
it'll all work out.

991
01:13:37,073 --> 01:13:38,983
Hey, Jasmine.

992
01:13:59,311 --> 01:14:00,824
Hey, Hank.

993
01:14:01,710 --> 01:14:05,259
You've made me real mad.

994
01:14:06,830 --> 01:14:08,309
About what?

995
01:14:08,470 --> 01:14:10,381
What do you think?

996
01:14:10,550 --> 01:14:13,621
I know you were out on that lake
with her.

997
01:14:13,869 --> 01:14:17,099
It makes me sick
to think of you and her.

998
01:14:17,269 --> 01:14:19,579
- Nothing happened.
- Oh, right.

999
01:14:19,748 --> 01:14:21,819
Nothing happened!

1000
01:14:21,989 --> 01:14:24,059
Come on, tough guy!
Come on, country boy!

1001
01:14:24,228 --> 01:14:26,867
You wanna take a shot at me, huh?
Come on!

1002
01:14:27,029 --> 01:14:29,702
- What are you doing?
- Come on, country boy, get up! Let's go.

1003
01:14:30,269 --> 01:14:31,826
Are you paranoid or something?

1004
01:14:34,389 --> 01:14:35,946
No.

1005
01:14:36,708 --> 01:14:38,857
But I'm a little confused.

1006
01:14:46,668 --> 01:14:49,022
I suppose you and her
will be getting married now.

1007
01:14:55,347 --> 01:14:57,336
It's the Southern way.

1008
01:14:57,506 --> 01:15:00,100
Man and woman as one.

1009
01:15:00,427 --> 01:15:05,658
Make sacrifices to build equity
in a future that has security.

1010
01:15:06,105 --> 01:15:08,573
Why do you sound like
a Mutual of Omaha ad?

1011
01:15:08,866 --> 01:15:10,821
Fine, joke it up.

1012
01:15:10,986 --> 01:15:13,100
At least I was prepared to marry her.

1013
01:15:15,665 --> 01:15:17,143
She's not in love with you.

1014
01:15:18,264 --> 01:15:20,858
Okay. That's the only
roadblock, though.

1015
01:15:24,385 --> 01:15:26,339
Let me ask you something.

1016
01:15:27,263 --> 01:15:30,972
Don't you think a guy is entitled
to choose his own destiny?

1017
01:15:31,544 --> 01:15:34,137
Whether it's in a small town
or even in California.

1018
01:15:34,303 --> 01:15:36,657
It's just that he shouldn't have it
handed to him.

1019
01:15:36,823 --> 01:15:40,054
Not like it's a... You know, like...

1020
01:15:40,222 --> 01:15:41,814
A hat?

1021
01:15:43,822 --> 01:15:46,052
Right. Okay, good. Like a hat.

1022
01:15:46,221 --> 01:15:49,373
Your father and your grandfather wore it,
now you're stuck with it.

1023
01:15:49,541 --> 01:15:52,136
Only the damn thing is too small.
It just doesn't fit.

1024
01:15:52,302 --> 01:15:57,329
- I hate a tight hat.
- There's a lot of hats out there.

1025
01:15:57,581 --> 01:16:01,130
And even if this one fits...

1026
01:16:01,302 --> 01:16:03,019
...and I'm not saying that it does...

1027
01:16:03,180 --> 01:16:07,092
...how do you know it's the right one
when you haven't tried any others on?

1028
01:16:07,260 --> 01:16:09,377
I sure haven't.

1029
01:16:10,900 --> 01:16:13,208
I mean, that's what
I'm talking about.

1030
01:16:14,261 --> 01:16:16,899
I just don't wanna screw up her life.

1031
01:16:18,059 --> 01:16:20,096
You know, Hollywood...

1032
01:16:20,259 --> 01:16:24,410
...sometimes a man's gotta do
what a man's gotta do.

1033
01:16:24,579 --> 01:16:29,289
And maybe...
Maybe it's in California.

1034
01:16:31,258 --> 01:16:33,567
Yeah, maybe you're right.

1035
01:16:34,738 --> 01:16:38,650
- Well, I'm glad we got that cleaned up.
- Me too, Hank.

1036
01:16:38,818 --> 01:16:41,207
Don't that take the rag off the bush?

1037
01:16:41,377 --> 01:16:43,651
Don't forget what I told you.

1038
01:17:44,572 --> 01:17:45,847
Hey, please!

1039
01:17:49,493 --> 01:17:51,402
Shit.

1040
01:18:00,130 --> 01:18:02,007
Shit.

1041
01:18:02,210 --> 01:18:03,849
Shit.

1042
01:18:15,410 --> 01:18:17,128
Dr. Stone.

1043
01:18:17,290 --> 01:18:19,325
Mary. Decided to drop by,
see how you were doing.

1044
01:18:19,489 --> 01:18:23,483
No damn good. Water's broke. I hurt.
This ain't like none of the others.

1045
01:18:23,649 --> 01:18:25,525
They never are.

1046
01:18:26,488 --> 01:18:29,481
Did Doc Hogue tell you this baby
might come out the wrong way?

1047
01:18:30,649 --> 01:18:33,242
He's coming.
He don't care which way.

1048
01:18:34,848 --> 01:18:38,045
- Fiddlesticks. Don't push, Mary.
- I can run, get an ambulance.

1049
01:18:38,208 --> 01:18:41,723
There's no time for that. Go into my
duffle bag, there's four clean shirts.

1050
01:18:41,887 --> 01:18:44,639
Get them and rip them
into even pieces.

1051
01:18:45,446 --> 01:18:49,155
Listen, Mary, don't push. I know
you want to, but don't push.

1052
01:18:49,327 --> 01:18:51,760
I'll try to turn him around
so he comes the right way.

1053
01:18:52,366 --> 01:18:54,243
Is it these ones?

1054
01:18:54,406 --> 01:18:58,685
- "Aramana"?
- Armani. Those are the ones.

1055
01:19:02,925 --> 01:19:06,680
Okay, now. Now! That's it.
Great. Great. Great.

1056
01:19:06,844 --> 01:19:08,881
Okay, okay, okay.

1057
01:19:09,565 --> 01:19:13,035
Now go! Push. Push, Mary.
You're doing great.

1058
01:19:13,204 --> 01:19:15,240
You're doing great.

1059
01:19:15,724 --> 01:19:17,716
I got a leg. I got a leg.

1060
01:19:25,523 --> 01:19:28,800
All right. Go ahead, go ahead.

1061
01:19:29,364 --> 01:19:31,159
Someone's coming.

1062
01:19:31,323 --> 01:19:34,234
Doc, someone's coming.

1063
01:19:35,003 --> 01:19:36,880
Okay, all right.

1064
01:19:41,482 --> 01:19:43,359
Push! Push, Mary!

1065
01:19:52,841 --> 01:19:54,116
Doc, your car.

1066
01:19:56,282 --> 01:19:57,794
What do I do?

1067
01:19:59,121 --> 01:20:00,793
Okay.

1068
01:20:01,960 --> 01:20:04,156
- Good girl!
- What do I do?

1069
01:20:04,320 --> 01:20:05,594
Push, Mary.

1070
01:20:09,520 --> 01:20:11,112
It's a girl!

1071
01:20:44,918 --> 01:20:47,384
I think I can fix that.

1072
01:21:02,035 --> 01:21:05,027
- You rang?
- First breech you ever delivered?

1073
01:21:06,515 --> 01:21:08,710
First baby I ever delivered.

1074
01:21:08,876 --> 01:21:10,148
By myself.

1075
01:21:11,035 --> 01:21:13,502
- Whiskey?
- No, thanks.

1076
01:21:13,673 --> 01:21:16,109
In fact, I wouldn't recommend that
for you, either.

1077
01:21:16,275 --> 01:21:18,835
You're not my doctor,
and you're not my wife...

1078
01:21:18,994 --> 01:21:21,952
...so I guess you don't have
very much to say about it.

1079
01:21:24,274 --> 01:21:27,073
You're not fixing to stay, huh, Stone?

1080
01:21:27,233 --> 01:21:29,464
Changed your mind, huh?

1081
01:21:29,633 --> 01:21:32,194
Now that your car's
all busted to bubkes...

1082
01:21:32,353 --> 01:21:35,981
...and you're feeling pretty good
about yourself in general, huh?

1083
01:21:37,752 --> 01:21:39,028
Come here.

1084
01:21:46,952 --> 01:21:49,227
I had them up once.

1085
01:21:49,392 --> 01:21:53,180
Over 700 babies I delivered
in this town over the years.

1086
01:21:53,351 --> 01:21:54,626
Nurse Packer.

1087
01:21:54,792 --> 01:21:59,659
She popped right out complete with
teeth and hair and bit me. An omen.

1088
01:21:59,831 --> 01:22:01,105
Nicholson.

1089
01:22:01,271 --> 01:22:02,909
Hank.

1090
01:22:03,869 --> 01:22:08,625
I gave them birth, saw them through
every sneeze and sniffle...

1091
01:22:08,791 --> 01:22:11,987
...and sometimes even walked them
to the gravesite.

1092
01:22:12,710 --> 01:22:16,497
They're pretty well
my portfolio, Stone.

1093
01:22:16,669 --> 01:22:20,868
That and an old car, an old house.

1094
01:22:21,229 --> 01:22:24,346
I wouldn't trade any of them for gold.

1095
01:22:25,149 --> 01:22:27,265
Well, maybe gold.

1096
01:22:27,909 --> 01:22:30,138
Or cash money.

1097
01:22:33,548 --> 01:22:35,344
- Hey.
- Doc.

1098
01:22:36,308 --> 01:22:38,104
Hey, Mary, how's our girl?

1099
01:22:38,268 --> 01:22:41,942
We decided she's gonna be
"Benjamina," after you.

1100
01:22:42,788 --> 01:22:44,584
What?

1101
01:22:45,347 --> 01:22:47,098
Thank you.

1102
01:22:47,547 --> 01:22:50,619
There's an obstetrician coming up
from Athens General later...

1103
01:22:50,787 --> 01:22:53,141
...just to make sure everything's okay.

1104
01:22:54,346 --> 01:22:55,938
Benjamina.

1105
01:22:57,746 --> 01:23:02,024
Yo, doc, I wanted to just thank you
for, you know, everything...

1106
01:23:02,186 --> 01:23:05,063
...so I made you this in appreciation.

1107
01:23:05,746 --> 01:23:10,865
I know it ain't very much, so if there's
ever anything at all I can do for you...

1108
01:23:11,026 --> 01:23:15,336
Just let me know what happens
with Ellen, Jimmy Joe and the Pakistani.

1109
01:23:34,582 --> 01:23:36,698
I heard what happened last night.
You did great.

1110
01:23:37,463 --> 01:23:41,580
- I didn't know what I was doing.
- Well, sometimes that's the best way.

1111
01:23:42,983 --> 01:23:44,859
There's something
that I wanted to say.

1112
01:23:45,022 --> 01:23:48,856
Something I wanted to say
to you first. Is that okay?

1113
01:23:49,422 --> 01:23:53,700
So I've been doing a lot of thinking
about last night.

1114
01:23:53,862 --> 01:23:56,660
Last night was really difficult.

1115
01:23:56,942 --> 01:24:01,651
Everything's all turned around now.
I've been thinking about you and me...

1116
01:24:01,820 --> 01:24:05,210
...and big cities, small towns...
- Well, I'm gonna marry Hank.

1117
01:24:07,261 --> 01:24:09,251
I've decided.

1118
01:24:13,179 --> 01:24:15,136
It's a plane ticket to Los Angeles.

1119
01:24:15,739 --> 01:24:17,537
The whole town chipped in.

1120
01:24:17,700 --> 01:24:22,454
We've kept you here this long, and if you
wait for Melvin to fix your car again...

1121
01:24:24,500 --> 01:24:26,693
You got Los Angeles waiting for you.

1122
01:24:26,858 --> 01:24:29,771
I've got Emma. It's not fair to you.

1123
01:24:29,938 --> 01:24:32,770
Hank's steady, and he's here.

1124
01:24:32,938 --> 01:24:34,577
You...

1125
01:24:35,338 --> 01:24:39,250
You're like a big, bright shooting star and
you're right, Ben, you'd burn out here.

1126
01:24:44,576 --> 01:24:46,170
Wait a minute.

1127
01:24:51,535 --> 01:24:54,654
Well, Ben Stone, you have five minutes
to say goodbye to Shangri-la.

1128
01:24:54,817 --> 01:24:58,206
Cotton will give you a police escort
to the airport.

1129
01:25:05,335 --> 01:25:07,611
We made you a sack lunch.

1130
01:25:07,775 --> 01:25:10,085
Airplane food can cause gas.

1131
01:25:15,935 --> 01:25:18,084
I guess I'll watch after your pig.

1132
01:25:18,254 --> 01:25:21,486
Just hope she takes to the farm
after living in town like this.

1133
01:25:22,134 --> 01:25:24,012
Appreciate it.

1134
01:25:24,454 --> 01:25:26,887
A lot of folks around here
gonna miss you.

1135
01:25:27,693 --> 01:25:31,082
I don't mean me.
But a lot of folks.

1136
01:26:01,730 --> 01:26:03,163
Adieu.

1137
01:26:11,570 --> 01:26:14,209
Back to the interstate,
Ben Stone, huh?

1138
01:26:14,370 --> 01:26:15,767
Back to the interstate.

1139
01:27:43,682 --> 01:27:45,558
You okay?

1140
01:27:46,403 --> 01:27:48,836
Oh, yes, I am fine.

1141
01:27:53,562 --> 01:27:57,157
Good morning, Halberstrom Clinic.
Could you hold, please.

1142
01:27:57,322 --> 01:28:01,234
Good morning, Halberstrom Clinic.
Good morning, Halberstrom Clinic.

1143
01:28:02,560 --> 01:28:04,676
Oh, hold. Yes, doctor.

1144
01:28:05,481 --> 01:28:07,597
- Mr. Stone?
- Dr. Stone.

1145
01:28:09,720 --> 01:28:11,676
Dr. Halberstrom can see you now.

1146
01:28:25,799 --> 01:28:28,949
Do you have any idea how many
applications I went through this year?

1147
01:28:29,118 --> 01:28:31,838
Yes, sir. That's why I knew
this interview was important.

1148
01:28:31,999 --> 01:28:34,717
I would've been here earlier
if I could've been. I think...

1149
01:28:34,878 --> 01:28:39,268
I know you're a great surgeon, Stone.
That whole pile is full of great surgeons.

1150
01:28:39,637 --> 01:28:41,468
Did you expect special consideration...

1151
01:28:41,638 --> 01:28:43,549
...because we're from
the same hometown?

1152
01:28:43,717 --> 01:28:45,787
- Because I knew your father?
- No, sir.

1153
01:28:45,957 --> 01:28:48,517
Good. Because you didn't get shit.

1154
01:28:48,677 --> 01:28:52,908
You wouldn't be here at all if it weren't
for a call I got from Dr. Aurelius Hogue.

1155
01:28:55,156 --> 01:28:56,588
Dr. Hogue called you?

1156
01:28:56,756 --> 01:28:59,669
I saw two doctors last week
with more experience than you...

1157
01:28:59,836 --> 01:29:02,429
...and better board certification scores.

1158
01:29:03,636 --> 01:29:06,547
Dr. Hogue's a piece of work, isn't he?

1159
01:29:06,876 --> 01:29:08,194
What did he say?

1160
01:29:08,354 --> 01:29:11,985
That you were doing volunteer
family practice down South somewhere.

1161
01:29:13,995 --> 01:29:17,748
Yes. Yeah. Yes, yes, that's right.

1162
01:29:18,475 --> 01:29:21,989
Went there to get that small-town chip
off your shoulder, didn't you?

1163
01:29:22,154 --> 01:29:26,114
- Yeah.
- Well, you're braver than I was, Stone.

1164
01:29:26,274 --> 01:29:29,311
Any case,
Hogue said you were, quote:

1165
01:29:29,474 --> 01:29:33,261
"One hellaciously fine physician."

1166
01:29:33,432 --> 01:29:37,108
That I would be "a bovine,
clodpated, citified moron"...

1167
01:29:37,273 --> 01:29:39,628
...if I didn't hire you on the spot.

1168
01:29:39,793 --> 01:29:41,670
I wrote it down so I wouldn't forget.

1169
01:29:41,833 --> 01:29:44,471
So I guess you're in, Stone. Congrats.

1170
01:29:44,632 --> 01:29:46,542
What time do I tee off?

1171
01:29:46,712 --> 01:29:48,862
You do play golf, don't you?

1172
01:29:49,031 --> 01:29:52,229
Great. Don't worry about that.
It's not anywhere you can see it.

1173
01:29:52,391 --> 01:29:56,144
The secret to this business is to get
a good pace going for yourself.

1174
01:29:56,310 --> 01:29:59,986
Nobody likes to admit it,
but medicine's a volume business.

1175
01:30:00,151 --> 01:30:02,744
Ninety-nine percent of what we do
is boilerplate surgery.

1176
01:30:02,909 --> 01:30:05,629
It means we can afford
the one percent that's meaningful.

1177
01:30:05,790 --> 01:30:09,385
Disfigurements, birth defects,
hare lips.

1178
01:30:10,350 --> 01:30:13,501
Cleft palates.
You live for those moments.

1179
01:30:13,669 --> 01:30:15,706
The bigger you get, the bigger the nut.

1180
01:30:15,869 --> 01:30:19,545
We're a service industry. Comes with
the territory. Fixed costs, specialization.

1181
01:30:19,710 --> 01:30:22,347
People adjust to it or fail.
Look at cable TV.

1182
01:30:22,509 --> 01:30:24,625
You're gonna see
some changes, Stone.

